dashboardItems.text:
*AV.7. Early viral load testing (at 6 months)* 
Cases on ART who had viral load monitoring at 6 months after initiation of ART 

Numerator: ART patients with a VL result at a visit 6 months after ART initiation in period. 
Denominator: ART patients with a visit 6 months after initiation in period. The case must have crossed "6 months after ART initiation" milestone after the start of period and before end.


*AV.3. PLHIV who have suppressed VL* Cases on ART (for at least 6 months) who have virological suppression, regardless of initiation date

Numerator: Cases on ART 6 months with at least one routine VL test result who have virological suppression (<1000 copies/mL) during the reporting period
Denominator: Cases on ART least 6 months with at least one routine VL result during the reporting period

*Viral Load (VL) testing Coverage and Suppression*

*AV.6 Annual VL Coverage*
Numerator: ART patients with at least one routine VL test result during the reporting period 
Denominator: ART patients on ART at least 6 months*

*CURRENT year measures all those who initiated treatment in first half of current year (or at least 6 months ago) and have VL test; prior year includes all who initiated treatment last calendar year

Viral Load Suppressed: Cumulative cases with latest recorded VL test result indicated VL suppression, divided by all cases with at least one VL test. Result did *not* need to occur this period.

PLHIV on ART >6 months and Ever Received VL Result: All cases with at least one VL result, divided by cumulative cases with at least one visit 6 months after ART initiation. VL result did *not* need to occur this period.

dashboardItems.text:
*Visits Within Period*

*TB.1. TPT initiation*
Numerator: Initiated treatment within reporting period. 
Denominator: all cases eligible for TPT treatment. Assumes receives TPT when first considered eligible.

*TPT Completion*
Numerator: ART patients who completed a course of TPT during the reporting period.
Denominator: ART patients who initiated any course of TPT *during the same reporting period*
This indicator will be lower than cumulative completion rate as it assumes both initiation and regimen completion within same year. This is distinct from *TB.2* which measures TPT initiation in previous reporting period.

*TB Prevention Therapy (TPT) Initiation & Completion*

_TPT Initiation_ : Eligible PLHIV
on ART who initiated TB preventive
treatment, cumulative.

_TPT Completion_ : PLHIV on ART who completed a course of TB preventive treatment among those who initiated TPT, cumulative.

All indicators on this dashboard exclude cases marked "died" or "lost to follow up", but may include cases which stopped TPT treatment and later resumed treatment. 
PLHIV on ART are not eligible for TPT if they exhibit certain co-morbidities, including active hepatitis, chronic alcoholism and/or neuropathy
*BE ADVISED*: Unless otherwise noted, population-level indicators use the official Spectrum-based estimate of PLHIV in denominators, which may not reflect the latest figures reported.

*HIV CS CASCADE*

For each period and count, total excludes cases where latest status was "DEAD" or "TRANSFER OUT". Totals are cumulative where noted. 

*TL.1 PLHIV Who Know Their Status (%)*: All cases in HIV CS Tracker divided by official estimate
*AV.2 PLHIV on ART (%)* :Cases on ART in HIV CS Tracker, divided by official estimate
*AV.3 PLHIV Who ave Suppressed VL (%)*: PLHIV with suppressed VL, divided by all cases with any VL test in HIV CS Tracker

*PLHIV Official Spectrum Estimate*: Spectrum-based national estimate for PLHIV (this year)
*People Living With HIV*: All cases in HIV CS Tracker
*PLHIV on ART*: All cases in HIV CS Tracker and on ART
*PLHIV eligible for viral load test*: Must have had positive HIV test results at least 6 months before the latest visit.
*PLHIV who have viral load results*: Must have had positive HIV test results at least 6 months before the latest event, and had VL result reported.
*PLHIV who have viral load suppression*: Must have had positive HIV test results 6 months before the latest event, and had VL result reported, where VL < 1000.
